# phase-leaguepicker-polish.log

v1.96.1 — LeaguePicker (LeagueSwitcherTabs) visual polish on `/test`.

Owner: claude (festive-maxwell-478c2c).

## M1 — audit + survey

### Current LeagueSwitcherTabs (post-v1.93.0 PR #263)

`src/components/homepage/LeagueSwitcherTabs.tsx`:

```
<nav className="w-full overflow-x-auto no-scrollbar mb-3">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 min-w-max">
    <Link
      className="flex-shrink-0 inline-flex items-center h-9 px-4 rounded-full
                 text-[11px] font-black uppercase tracking-widest
                 transition-transform duration-100 active:scale-[0.96]
                 ${selected ? 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground'
                            : 'bg-surface text-fg-mid hover:bg-surface-md'}"
    >
      {leagueName}
      {showSpinner && (
        <span className="ml-1.5 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full
                         bg-current opacity-70 animate-pulse" />
      )}
    </Link>
  </div>
</nav>
```

### Findings against the four reported issues

**(1) Spacing.** Switcher is rendered inside the Dashboard `topSlot` slot,
which sits BETWEEN `main`'s `pt-12` (header reservation, 48px) and
`<div className="animate-in pt-2">`. So `topSlot` gets 0px above and the
switcher pill row sits flush at the 48px line. RecruitingBanner gets
8px via the `pt-2` inside `animate-in`.

Fix: add 8–12px of top padding to the switcher container (or to the
`<MultiLeagueHub>` `topSlot` wrapper). Going with `pt-2` on the
switcher itself so the spacing is colocated with the component.

**(2) Scrollbar.** `no-scrollbar` hides the scrollbar entirely.
`globals.css` has `.scrollbar-hide` which is the same intent under a
different name. No styled-scrollbar utility exists. Need a new utility
class that surfaces a thin horizontal scrollbar styled with the
design tokens.

Plan:
- Add `.picker-scrollbar` utility in `globals.css`:
  - `scrollbar-width: thin; scrollbar-color: var(--fg-low) transparent;` (Firefox)
  - `::-webkit-scrollbar { height: 4px; }`
  - `::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; border-radius: 9999px; }`
  - `::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--fg-low); border-radius: 9999px; }`
  - `::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover { background: var(--fg-mid); }`
  - `::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:active { background: var(--primary); }`

**(3) Distinct visual treatment.** Pills are 36px tall with 11px text
— small and easily missed. The active pill differs from inactive only
by background fill. Touch target on iOS WCAG/HIG: ≥44×44px.

Plan:
- Bump height: `h-9` → `h-11` (44px) for touch-target compliance.
- Bump padding: `px-4` → `px-5`.
- Bump text: `text-[11px]` → `text-[12px]` (still uppercase, font-black, tracking-widest).
- Active pill:
  - `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`
  - `border-2 border-primary` (visual weight)
  - `shadow-[0_2px_10px_rgba(233,0,82,0.4)]` — uses the existing
    `--glow-primary-bar` recipe inline (the var is in `:root` but Tailwind v4
    `shadow-[var(--glow-primary-bar)]` should resolve at build time).
    Using inline rgba is safer than a CSS var arbitrary value.
- Inactive pill:
  - `bg-surface text-fg-mid border border-border-default`
  - Hover: `hover:bg-surface-md hover:text-fg-high`
- Need vertical padding INSIDE the scroll viewport so the active
  pill's glow isn't clipped at the top/bottom of the overflow
  container — putting `py-2` on the inner `flex` div gives the
  shadow 8px of safety on each side.

**(4) Loading animation standardization.** Survey of existing patterns:

| Pattern | Files | Use case |
|---|---|---|
| `border-2 border-{color} border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin` | RsvpButton, RsvpBar | Inline pending button cue |
| `Loader2 animate-spin` (lucide) | admin SettingsTab, LeagueFeesEditor, LeaguePlannedRosterEditor, etc. | Admin pending button cue |
| `animate-pulse` on `bg-surface-md` block | Dashboard widgets, StatsDashboard, LineLoginButton | Below-fold widget skeleton |
| `animate-hub-progress` 2px top strip | HubTransitionShell | Page-level nav transition cue |
| `animate-pulse` 1.5×1.5px dot | LeagueSwitcherTabs (current) | Per-tab pending cue |

Predominant inline-pending pattern across non-admin public UI: the
`animate-spin` ring (RsvpButton). Per-tab pending cue should match
that, not the bespoke pulsing dot.

Plan: replace the dot with a small spinning ring:
```
<span className="ml-2 inline-block h-3 w-3 border-2 border-current
                 border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin
                 opacity-80" />
```

The top-edge progress strip via HubTransitionShell stays as-is — it
serves a different role (page-level nav state, not per-tab).

**(5) Pending-tab bug verification.**
Source: `selected = m.leagueId === optimisticActiveId`, `showSpinner = isPending && selected`.
`setOptimisticActiveId(leagueId)` runs inside `startNavigation(() => {...})`.
React 19 useOptimistic guarantees the value is visible WITHIN the
transition's render — so on click, the just-clicked pill's `selected`
becomes true SAME tick as `isPending` becomes true. Spinner fires on
the just-clicked pill, not the old active one. Confirmed in
`v193_league_picker_perf.test.ts` lines 299–309.

→ No regression. Will add an additional explicit re-pin in
`v1961_league_picker_polish.test.ts` so the relationship is
double-locked against future refactor.

## M2 / M3 / M4 — implementation

All three milestones touched the SAME single JSX file
(`src/components/homepage/LeagueSwitcherTabs.tsx`) plus one CSS file
(`src/app/globals.css`), so they shipped in one bundled edit:

### `src/app/globals.css` — new `.picker-scrollbar` utility

```css
.picker-scrollbar {
  scrollbar-width: thin;
  scrollbar-color: var(--fg-low) transparent;
}
.picker-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar { height: 4px; }
.picker-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; border-radius: 9999px; }
.picker-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--fg-low); border-radius: 9999px; }
.picker-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover { background: var(--fg-mid); }
.picker-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:active { background: var(--primary); }
```

### `src/components/homepage/LeagueSwitcherTabs.tsx`

Outer nav:
- `w-full overflow-x-auto no-scrollbar mb-3` → `w-full overflow-x-auto picker-scrollbar pt-2 mb-4`
  - `pt-2` (8px) breathing room below the fixed Header.
  - `picker-scrollbar` surfaces the styled thin horizontal scrollbar.
  - `mb-4` (16px, was `mb-3`/12px) breathing before the recruiting-banner stack.

Inner flex container:
- `flex items-center gap-2 min-w-max` → `flex items-center gap-2 min-w-max py-2`
  - `py-2` reserves 8px above + below pills inside the scroll viewport so
    the active-pill glow shadow isn't clipped by `overflow-x-auto`.

Pills (Link):
- `h-9 px-4` → `h-11 px-5` (44px touch-compliant).
- `text-[11px]` → `text-[12px]` (still uppercase + tracking-widest + font-black).
- `transition-transform duration-100` → `transition-all duration-150`
  (border + shadow + colour now animate together).
- Active: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground` → `bg-primary text-primary-foreground border-2 border-primary shadow-[0_2px_10px_rgba(233,0,82,0.4)]`.
- Inactive: `bg-surface text-fg-mid hover:bg-surface-md` → `bg-surface text-fg-mid border border-border-default hover:bg-surface-md hover:text-fg-high hover:border-border-default`.

Per-tab spinner:
- `ml-1.5 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-current opacity-70 animate-pulse`
- → `ml-2 inline-block h-3 w-3 border-2 border-current border-t-transparent rounded-full animate-spin opacity-80`
- Matches `RsvpButton` / `RsvpBar` inline pending pattern.

## M4 — pending-tab bug verification

Confirmed unchanged: `selected = m.leagueId === optimisticActiveId` and
`showSpinner = isPending && selected`. The optimistic id is set inside
`startNavigation(() => { setOptimisticActiveId(leagueId); router.push(href, …) })`
so the spinner attaches to the just-clicked pill (not the previously-
active one). Already pinned in v1.93.0 — added an additional explicit
re-pin in `v1961_league_picker_polish.test.ts` so any future refactor
that re-introduces the bug fails BOTH suites.

